 should attend?**\n* Market participants\n* Local regulatory authority\n* Entity representing a market participant  ...    Step 1: join web conference at https://caiso.webex.com/caiso/j.php?MTID=m3c58e1255471fcbcbe28ab8532673ac8  ...    Audio only participation: call 1-844-621-3956 with access code 2493 529 8252. Technical support: Go to https://help.webex.com  ...    View more events under Business Practice Manual (BPM) change management\n05/19/2026\n#####\nClose View agendas, presentations and recordings of previous BPM meetings.\n## BPM change management process The ISO systematic and publicly transparent BPM Change Management process ensures the consideration of all relevant information when modifying BPMs. The change management process uses a system available through the ISO public website that provides a way to propose BPM changes, comment on open change requests, and track proposed change requests. The change management process begins when the ISO or a stakeholder submits a web-based Proposed Revision Request (PRR). After an ISO review for completeness, PRRs are posted to the website, triggering a stakeholder review and comment  ...    1. **Submit Proposed Revision Request (PRR)**\n2. **Comments period** Upon ISO acceptance, PRR becomes public and 10-business day comment period starts\n3. **Stakeholder meeting**  ...    \\*Stakeholders have the right to appeal the final decision of a proposed revision request (PRR)\n \n## Appeals Stakeholders have the right to appeal the final decision of a proposed revision request (PRR). Upon appeal, an ISO executive appeals"
